<ResourceLayout 
  name="New Client"
  description="Getting started with Twilight Psychology"
>
  <h2>Welcome!</h2>
  <p>
    We're glad you've chosen Twilight Psychology. Our goal is to make your first experience with us as smooth and comfortable as possible. Here's what you can expect.
  </p>

  <h2>Step 1: Schedule Your Appointment</h2>
  <p>
    Contact our office to book your initial appointment. We'll ask about your primary concerns and any scheduling preferences. You can schedule online, by phone, or through our contact form.
  </p>

  <h2>Step 2: Complete Intake Forms</h2>
  <p>
    Before your appointment, you'll receive intake forms to complete. These help us understand your background, medical history, and current concerns. Please bring completed forms to your appointment, or arrive 15 minutes early to complete them in person.
  </p>

  <h2>Step 3: Insurance Verification</h2>
  <p>
    If you have insurance, we can verify your coverage for you. Please have your insurance card ready when scheduling. If paying out-of-pocket, we accept multiple payment methods.
  </p>

  <h2>What to Bring</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Valid photo ID</li>
    <li>Insurance card (if applicable)</li>
    <li>Completed intake forms</li>
    <li>List of current medications (if applicable)</li>
    <li>Any relevant medical or psychiatric records</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>First Appointment</h2>
  <p>
    During your first appointment, we'll discuss your concerns, medical history, and goals for treatment. This is also your opportunity to ask questions about our services and approach. We strive to create a warm, non-judgmental environment where you feel heard and supported.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions Before Your Visit?</h2>
  <p>
    Don't hesitate to reach out. <a href="https://heatherlcornett.clientsecure.me/contact-widget" target="_blank">Contact us</a> with any questions about preparing for your appointment.
  </p>
</ResourceLayout>
